NotateDiary
===========

The diary of Tom Riddle, for Onyx BOOX & Android E-Ink tablets.

This product includes software developed by third parties. We are grateful to
the following open-source projects and their authors.


Upstream projects / 上游项目
----------------------------

1. Notate — the handwriting / note-taking engine
     https://github.com/alexdremov/notate
     Copyright (c) Aleksandr Dremov
     License: MIT

     NotateDiary is built directly on top of the Notate codebase (infinite
     canvas, stroke rendering, E-Ink optimizations, sync, export). The original
     MIT license and copyright are retained in LICENSE.

2. riddle — the enchanted diary of Tom Riddle (the original concept)
     https://github.com/MaximeRivest/riddle
     Copyright (c) Maxime Rivest
     License: MIT

     The creative concept and core interaction of the enchanted diary — write in
     ink, the diary drinks your words, and an answer writes itself back in a
     flowing hand — originate from riddle, which targets the reMarkable Paper
     Pro. NotateDiary ports this experience to Android / BOOX E-Ink devices and
     re-implements it on the Notate engine with an LLM as the diary's "spirit".


Modifications in this derivative work / 本衍生作品的修改
------------------------------------------------------

  * Ported the enchanted-diary interaction to Android (Jetpack Compose) and
    Onyx BOOX E-Ink devices.
  * Added the AI Diary feature package `com.alexdremov.notate.ai`:
    handwriting capture, OpenAI-compatible vision-LLM client, persona (Tom
    Riddle) prompting, ink-bleed reveal / fade-out animations, and bilingual
    (CN/EN) reply behavior.
  * Added encrypted API-key storage (EncryptedSharedPreferences).
  * Re-themed the canvas as a parchment diary page with a handwritten reply
    typeface.

These modifications and additions are also released under the MIT License.


